DPRK Magicians Association founded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Magicians Association was founded in Pyongyang yesterday.
 The objective of the association grouping magic experts and fans is to contribute to the development of the country's magic and the creative activities of the magicians and strengthen the exchange and cooperation with international magic organizations and magicians bodies and magicians in different countries.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The association is headquartered in Pyongyang and has over 10 branches in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its chairman is famous juggler Kim Thaek Song, Labour Hero and People's Artiste of the DPRK.

Withdrawal of U.S. forces from S. Korea urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- The south headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) reportedly made public a statement on Oct. 18 denouncing the Bush administration for openly revealing its ambition for hegemony with the outcries for the permanent presence of the U.S. forces in South Korea.
 Condemning the U.S. forces for committing all sorts of heinous acts in South Korea, the statement noted that bush's remark in a recent interview revealed the U.S. aggressive nature as it was no more than an expression of his intention to turn away from peace and reunification on the Korean peninsula and resort to its permanent division and confrontation with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement urged bush to properly understand the South Korean people's daily mounting anti-U.S. feelings, sign a DPRK-U.S. peace agreement and withdraw the U.S. forces from South Korea, though belatedly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stressed that the students and people from every background will conduct a more vigorous movement for anti-U.S., anti-war, peace and withdrawal of the U.S. forces from South Korea and certainly open a new phase for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration and the independent reunification.

Seminars held in Italy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Seminars on the subject of "The Workers' Party of Korea and Its Historic Roots" and "the WPK, Revolutionary Party of Juche Type" were held by the Unified Communist Party of Italy and the Catania branch of the Italian committee for the study of the Juche idea on October 7 and 10 on the occasion of the 56th anniversary of the WPK and the 75th anniversary of the formation of the Down-With-Imperialism Union (DIU).
 The general secretary of the Unified Communist Party of Italy in a speech said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung formed the DIU on October 17, 1926. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK was founded on October 10, 1945, but it took its historic roots at the DIU.
 Working at the WPK Central Committee from 30 odd years ago leader Kim Jong Il has strengthened and developed the WPK as the glorious party of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the Catania branch of the Italian committee for the study of the Juche idea noted that Kim Il Sung founded the immortal Juche idea in his early years. It was thanks to this revolutionary idea that the Korean people could win in the struggle against Japanese imperialism and defeat U.S. imperialism in the three-year war, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has recently made great achievements in its foreign relations, he said, stressing this is the fruit of the wise leadership of the WPK which takes the Juche idea as its guiding idea.

20th national meeting of movement for supporting Korea's reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tokyo, October 23 (KNS-KCNA) -- The 20th national meeting of the movement for supporting Korea's reunification was held in Saitama prefecture, Japan, on Oct 20 and 21 under the sponsorship of the Japan committee for supporting the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea, the Japan-Korea Cultural Interchange Association, the Japan-Korea Society for Scientific and Educational Interchange, the Japan Women's Liaison Society for Solidarity with the Korean Women and the Saitama Prefectural Executive Committee.
 Jun Shimizu, secretary general of the Japan-Korea Cultural Interchange Association, in his report at the meeting said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Supporting the efforts to realize Korea's reunification is an important struggle for world peace at a time when the movement to hail and support the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea is gaining momentum worldwide after the publication of the north-south joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The current meeting will become a new starting point of the movement for supporting Korea's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Denouncing the U.S. and the Japanese government for their hostile policy toward the DPRK, He demanded the Japanese government make an official apology for Japan's aggression of Korea and colonial domination over it and fundamentally correct the policy related to the issue of the legal status of the Koreans in Japan for an early resumption of negotiations for the establishment of diplomatic relations between Japan and the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then, followed panel discussions on the subject of "trend of situation towards reunification", "for friendship and peace" and "ensurance of national education." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal, a special resolution and an emergency resolution were adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The documents called upon the Japanese government to stop at once its hostile policy toward the DPRK, resume negotiations for the establishment of diplomatic relations with the DPRK based on apology and compensation for Japan's colonial domination over Korea and protect human rights of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They rejected the investigation of the Japanese prosecutors' office into Japan-DPRK friendship organizations and stressed the need to develop the Japan-DPRK movement.

51st anniversary of CPV's entry into Korean front marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Newspapers here today dedicate articles to the 51st anniversary of the Chinese People's Volunteers' entry into the Korean front.
 Today 51 years ago the party and government of China dispatched the Chinese People's Volunteers consisting of good sons and daughters of the Chinese people to the Korean front under the banner of "resisting America and aiding Korea, safeguarding the home and defending the motherland." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On this occasion the officers and men of the people's army and people of Korea extend greetings to the officers and men of the people's liberation army and people of china and express noble respects to the fallen Chinese People's Volunteers, Rodong Sinmun in a signed article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The officers and men of the Chinese People's Volunteers valiantly fought in the same trench with the officers and men of the Korean People's Army and performed great feats.
 They displayed mass heroism and self-sacrificing spirit in numerous operations and contributed to the victory of the Korean people in the Great Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mountain ridges of Korea are permeated with their blood and associated with their feats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their entry into the Korean front powerfully demonstrated the might of long-standing korea-china friendship and deepened the bonds between the two peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of Korea-China friendship continues in the new century, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the will of the leaders of the two countries and the desire of the two peoples to steadily strengthen and develop Korea-China friendship in the 21st century.
 Korea-China friendship will be consolidated by the joint efforts of the two parties, two governments and two peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The feats performed by the CPV on the Korean front will shine long with the history of Korea-China friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that although more than a half century has passed since the CPV's entry into the Korean front, their heroic self-sacrificing spirit has been cherished in the hearts of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will as ever make efforts to develop Korea-China friendship together with the Chinese people, says the paper.
